abstract: With few tools to block a Supreme Court nominee, Democrats decided to test Senate rules and decorum at the hearings to confirm Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh.
snippet: With few tools to block a Supreme Court nominee, Democrats decided to test Senate rules and decorum at the hearings to confirm Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Boorish. Rude. Disrespectful. Insulting. Grandstanding. Hyperventilating. Deranged. Ridiculous. Drivel.

abstract: They’re not restraining Trump. They’re making him more powerful.
snippet: They’re not restraining Trump. They’re making him more powerful.
lead_paragraph: On Wednesday, the second day of Brett Kavanaugh’s Supreme Court confirmation hearing, Senator Kamala Harris, Democrat of California, asked him a straightforward question about Robert Mueller, the special counsel. “Have you discussed Mueller or his investigation with anyone at Kasowitz Benson and Torres, the law firm founded by Marc Kasowitz, President Trump’s personal lawyer?” Harris asked.

headline_main: The Corrupt Bargain of the Adults in the Room

abstract: From the moment Brett M. Kavanaugh’s confirmation hearings began, Senate Democrats considering a White House run have used the live television event as a proving ground.
snippet: From the moment Brett M. Kavanaugh’s confirmation hearings began, Senate Democrats considering a White House run have used the live television event as a proving ground.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The questioning of Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh had not even begun Thursday morning when Senator Cory Booker, Democrat of New Jersey, threatened to release secret emails — even if it meant being expelled from the Senate.

abstract: Republicans and Democrats sparred over censorship on social media, as the Justice Department said it would examine whether the services were purposely “stifling the free exchange of ideas.”
snippet: Republicans and Democrats sparred over censorship on social media, as the Justice Department said it would examine whether the services were purposely “stifling the free exchange of ideas.”
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Republicans accused Twitter of being biased against conservatives on Wednesday, drawing rebukes from Democrats in a congressional hearing that illustrated how partisan lines are increasingly being drawn on social media.

headline_main: California Today: California Tribes Confront History and Heroin
byline_original: By Jose A. Del Real and Matt Stevens

abstract: Confirmation hearings for the Supreme Court nominee Brett M. Kavanaugh opened with protests and theater, as Democrats unleashed a fierce barrage.
snippet: Confirmation hearings for the Supreme Court nominee Brett M. Kavanaugh opened with protests and theater, as Democrats unleashed a fierce barrage.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senate Democrats tore into President Trump’s Supreme Court nominee on Tuesday, painting Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh as a narrow-minded partisan as the opening day of his confirmation hearings verged on pandemonium. Dozens of screaming protesters were hauled out of the hearing room in handcuffs.

abstract: Framing the midterms as Election Day draws closer.
snippet: Framing the midterms as Election Day draws closer.
lead_paragraph: Frank Bruni: Summer is effectively over, September is upon us, the school year begins, and you, Ross, and I have a new homework assignment: For the next two months, we’ll alternate from one week to the next with our esteemed colleagues Gail Collins and Bret Stephens in conducting these conversations about current events. Here we go!
